Project_Title: High-throughput and automated acoustic trapping of extracellular vesicles to identify microRNAs with diagnostic potential for prostate cancer (human)
Project_Description:
We performed small RNA sequencing on 173 urinary extracellular vesicles derived from patients with either positive or negative prostate cancer biopsy in order to assess its potential as biomarkers.
Overall design: Comparison of the microRNA profile from urinary extracellular vesicles of patients with Gleason Grade Group ≥ 4 to patients with Gleason Grade Group ≤ 3, including patients with undetectable prostate cancer on biopsy.
